#
# # Biblical Foundation
#
# Scripture: "Let all things be done decently and in order."
# - 1 Corinthians 14:40
#
# Principle: Consistent formatting across all editors ensures code looks the
# same regardless of who writes it or what tool they use. EditorConfig
# establishes "decency and order" at the foundational level - before code
# is even written, the environment is configured for consistency.
#
# Anchor: "For God is not the author of confusion, but of peace."
# - 1 Corinthians 14:33
#
# # CPI-SI Identity
#
# Component Type: Rails
#
# EditorConfig provides infrastructure that affects ALL code editing across
# the project. It doesn't transform data (Baton) or provide foundations
# (Ladder), but ensures consistent formatting infrastructure for everyone.
#
# Role: Cross-editor formatting consistency enforcement
#
# Paradigm: CPI-SI framework component - editor configuration
#
# # Authorship & Lineage
#
#   - Architect: [Who designed these formatting standards]
#   - Implementation: [Who maintains this file]
#   - Created: [YYYY-MM-DD]
