# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Validation
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Verify EditorConfig is working:
#
#   # Check EditorConfig for a specific file
#   editorconfig [filename]
#
#   # In VS Code, check bottom status bar for "Spaces: 4" or "Tab Size: 4"
#
#   # Verify with editorconfig-checker tool
#   ec -config .editorconfig
#
# Common Issues:
#
#   "Settings not applied" - Check if editor has EditorConfig plugin
#   "Conflict with Prettier" - Ensure EditorConfig and Prettier agree
#   "Tabs in Go files showing wrong" - Tab display width is editor setting
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Modification Policy
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Safe to Modify:
#   ✅ Add new file type sections
#   ✅ Adjust indent_size for specific languages
#   ✅ Add project-specific overrides at bottom
#
# Modify with Care:
#   ⚠️ Changing indent_style for established file types
#   ⚠️ Changing end_of_line (affects all contributors)
#   ⚠️ Removing trim_trailing_whitespace (leads to noisy diffs)
#
# NEVER Modify:
#   ❌ charset = utf-8 (universal standard)
#   ❌ end_of_line = lf (Linux-first principle)
#   ❌ root = true (breaks configuration hierarchy)
#   ❌ Makefile tab requirement (syntax requirement)
#   ❌ 4-block documentation structure
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Integration with Other Tools
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# EditorConfig sets base formatting. Other tools build on it:
#
#   - Prettier: Respects EditorConfig, adds more formatting rules
#   - ESLint: Code quality + some formatting (prefer EditorConfig for basics)
#   - gofmt/rustfmt: Language formatters (may override EditorConfig)
#   - Git: Configure core.autocrlf=input to complement end_of_line=lf
#
# Recommended .gitattributes companion:
#   * text=auto eol=lf
#   *.{cmd,[cC][mM][dD]} text eol=crlf
#   *.{bat,[bB][aA][tT]} text eol=crlf
#
